The paper deals with human attribute and action recognition in still images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach to encoding multi-scale information in image representations, which involves deep learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on multiple datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
